    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Panels D-F show the presence of the terminal ending of a single neuron (arrow) and its axon (arrowhead) present in the dermis and labeled strongly for both integrin α2 (D) as well as for peripherin (E). Superimposed D and E images are shown in F, and indicate stronger co-localization of integrin α2 and peripherin at the receptive ending than at the axon of this neuron.\". Experimental description: \"Skin specimens were obtained from the medial thigh of the opposite hindlimbs of the rats used in the neurophysiological experiments.\"",
